body:
Hi all, 
I have the below code,
```Verilog
`timescale 100 ps / 100 ps

// `celldefine

// `suppress_faults
// `enable_portfaults

module dff(q,qb,clk,d,rst);
  input  d, clk, rst;
  output q, qb;

  dflop d1 (q_, d, clk, rst);
  buf   b1 (q, q_);
  not   n1 (qb, q);

endmodule

// `disable_portfaults
// `nosuppress_faults

// `endcelldefine

primitive dflop (q, d, clk, rst);
  input  d, clk, rst;
  output q;
  reg    q;

  table
  // d clk  rst : q_old : q_new
     ?  ?    0  :   ?   :   0;
     ?  ?    x  :   0   :   0;
     0  r    1  :   ?   :   0;
 //  0 (01)  1  :   ?   :   0;
     1  r    1  :   ?   :   1;
 //  1 (01)  1  :   ?   :   1;
     ?  f    1  :   ?   :   -;
 //  ? (10)  1  :   ?   :   -;
     *  ?    ?  :   ?   :   -;
     ?  ?    *  :   ?   :   -;
  endtable

endprimitive
```
and Yosys produces the below error:
```shell
yosys> read -sv dff.v 
1. Executing Verilog-2005 frontend: dff.v
Parsing SystemVerilog input from `dff.v' to AST representation.
dff.v:32: ERROR: syntax error, unexpected TOK_ID
```
Does it mean that Yosys doesn't support table primitive or keyword "primitive"?
Thanks

